[[Bill Bruford]], [[Robert Fripp]], and [[Tony Levin]], except where noted.\n\n# \"[[Elephant Talk]]\" \u2013 4:44\n# \"Frame by Frame\" \u2013 5:08\n# \"[[Matte Kudasai]]\" \u2013 3:46\n# \"[[Thela Hun Ginjeet]]\" \u2013 6:26\n# \"The Sheltering Sky\" \u2013 8:23\n# \"[[Discipline (instrumental)|Discipline]]\" \u2013 5:02\n# \"[[Heartbeat (King Crimson song)|Heartbeat]]\" \u2013 3:54\n# \"Waiting Man\" \u2013 4:26\n# \"Neurotica\" \u2013 4:49\n# \"Requiem\" \u2013 6:36\n# \"[[Three of a Perfect Pair (song)|Three of a Perfect Pair]]\" \u2013 4:10\n# \"[[Sleepless (King Crimson song)|Sleepless]]\" \u2013 5:24\n\n====Bonus tracks: 1983\u20132004====\n# \"The King Crimson Barber Shop\" (Levin) \u2013 1:36\n# \"Form No. 1\" (Fripp (???)) \u2013 3:03\n# \"Bude\" (Belew) \u2013 0:25\n# \"Potato Pie\" (abridged) (Belew, Fripp, [[Trey Gunn]], [[Pat Mastelotto]]) \u2013 4:33\n# \"Clouds\" (Belew) \u2013 0:33\n# \"Einstein's Relatives\" (Belew, Fripp, Gunn, Mastelotto) \u2013 3:08\n*Tracks 1-6 from ''[[Discipline (King Crimson album)|Discipline]]'' (1981)\n*Tracks 7-10 from ''[[Beat (King Crimson album)|Beat]]'' (1982)\n*Tracks 11-12 from ''[[Three of a Perfect Pair]]'' (1984)\n*Bonus track 1 from ''[[Frame by Frame: The Essential King Crimson]]'', ''[[Heartbeat: The Abbreviated King Crimson]]'' (both from 1991), and the 2001 reissue of ''Three of a Perfect Pair''\n*Bonus tracks 3-6 from the ''[[Happy with What You Have to Be Happy With]]'' [[Extended play|EP]] (2002)\n*Bonus track 2 previously unreleased (2005)\n\n===Disc Two: Live: 1981\u20131984===\nAll songs written by Belew, Bruford, Fripp, and Levin.\n\n# \"Entry of the Crims\" (Live at [[Spectrum (Montreal)|Le Spectrum]], [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]], 11 July 1984) \u2013 4:42\n# \"[[Larks' Tongues in Aspic (instrumental)#Part III|Larks' Tongues in Aspic Part III]]\" ([[Abridgement|Abridged]]) (Live at Le Spectrum, Montreal, [[Quebec]], Canada, 11 July 1984) \u2013 2:47\n# \"Thela Hun Ginjeet\" (Live at Le Spec